Title : Bonesgate Open Space
Text : [[File:Bonesgate Open Space 6.JPG|thumb]]
'''Bonesgate Open Space''' is a public park, [[Local Nature Reserve]] (LNR) and [[Site of Nature Conservation Interest|Site of Borough Importance for Nature Conservation]], Grade 1, in [[Chessington]] in the [[Royal Borough of Kingston upon Thames]] in London. It has an area of 5.07 hectares, and was designated an LNR in 1994.<ref name=LNR>{{cite web|url= http://www.lnr.naturalengland.org.uk/Special/lnr/lnr_details.asp?C=0&N=&ID=55|title= Bonesgate Open Space|series= Local Nature Reserves|publisher= Natural England|date= 1 March 2013|accessdate= 2 May 2014|deadurl= yes|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20140502220206/http://www.lnr.naturalengland.org.uk/Special/lnr/lnr_details.asp?C=0&N=&ID=55|archivedate= 2 May 2014|df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url= http://magic.defra.gov.uk/MagicMap.aspx?startTopic=Designations&activelayer=lnrIndex&query=REF_CODE%3D%271008794%27|title=Map of Bonesgate Open Space|series=Local Nature Reserves|publisher=Natural England|accessdate=  2 May 2014}}</ref><ref name=GIGL>{{cite web|url=http://www.gigl.org.uk/online/site-Details.aspx?sID=KiBI05&sType=sinc|title=Castle Hill and Bonesgate Open Space|publisher=Greenspace Information for Greater London|year=2013|accessdate= 2 May 2014}}</ref>

The site is a linear park along the banks of the [[Bonesgate Stream]] between Chessington Road and Filby Road. It adjoins [[Castle Hill, Chessington|Castle Hill]] LNR to the south and [[Hogsmill]] LNR (in [[Epsom and Ewell]]) to the north. It is mainly grassland with some coppiced hazel, which has the locally rare [[Ranunculus auricomus|goldilocks buttercup]]. Birds include the [[great spotted woodpecker]], [[song thrush]] and [[lesser whitethroat]].<ref name=GIGL/>

